message: "If you use this software, please cite it as below."
title: "0CompactMem: Full OS Memory Semantics for LLM Agent Persistence"
authors:
  - family-names: Su
    given-names: Zhidao
    email: soolaugust@gmail.com
type: software
license: MIT
repository-code: "https://github.com/soolaugust/0CompactMem"
url: "https://github.com/soolaugust/0CompactMem"
version: "0.1.0"
date-released: "2026-05-25"
keywords:
  - persistent memory
  - LLM agents
  - operating systems
  - memory management
  - MCP
  - demand paging
  - eviction
  - pinning
abstract: >-
  0CompactMem is an agent memory layer that implements the full spectrum
  of OS memory-management primitives for LLM agent persistence. It maps
  demand paging to on-demand retrieval, kswapd-style watermarks to
  capacity-aware eviction, mlock to hard/soft pin semantics, DAMON to
  access tracking, and CRIU to session checkpoint/restore. Implemented
  as a single SQLite file with an MCP-native interface.
